    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BRAKE BOOSTER AND MASTER CYLINDER - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0401702">Figure 2</hotlnk>
                for all items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <para>The Hydro-Max&#8482; booster (Item 1) converts hydraulic pressure from the power steering pump to
                mechanical force. This force is transmitted to the master cylinder (Item 2) which is mounted to the
                booster. The master cylinder converts the force from the booster to brake fluid pressure.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0401702" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg04/g0401722.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="432px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Hydro-Max&#8482; Booster and Backup Pump with Master Cylinder</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BOOSTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MASTER CYLINDER BODY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BOOSTER INLET PORT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BOOSTER OUTLET PORT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BACKUP PUMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. FLOW SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. RELAY</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. MASTER CYLINDER RESERVOIR</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. PRESSURE DIFFERENTIAL SWITCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
